                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.428/773</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        British Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chilton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-11-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The receipt is acknowledged of your note No. 995
                    of November 21, 1923, informing this Government that the Canadian Government has
                    decided that from the 31st of December, 1923, <hi rend="italic">modus
                        vivendi</hi> licenses as provided by Section 3 of Chapter 47 of the Revised
                    Statutes of Canada will not be issued to fishing vessels of the United States
                    and that after that date their rights will be governed only by the provisions of
                    the Treaty of 1818.</p>
                <p>Information as to the decision of the Canadian Government has been communicated
                    to the appropriate authorities of this Government in order that public
                    announcement may be made for the information of interested persons.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
